00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:09,767
- What do you mean?

618
00:33:09,791 --> 00:33:12,640
- Not so much as a burp
since yesterday afternoon.

619
00:33:26,622 --> 00:33:29,659
- So what are they gonna do?

620
00:33:29,683 --> 00:33:31,906
- In a word, nothing.

621
00:33:31,930 --> 00:33:32,930
- Nothing?

622
00:33:33,623 --> 00:33:34,966
- I guess the government's
decided to sit around

623
00:33:34,990 --> 00:33:36,276
with their thumbs up their butts

624
00:33:36,300 --> 00:33:37,616
till we're all knee deep lava

625
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:39,786
before they decide to do something.

626
00:33:39,810 --> 00:33:41,776
- A little more eloquent explanation,

627
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:42,800
thank you, Kai.

628
00:33:44,800 --> 00:33:46,223
Government wants proof.

629
00:33:47,350 --> 00:33:49,716
I guess we have to get it for 'em.

630
00:33:49,740 --> 00:33:52,146
Look, as you guys all know,

631
00:33:52,170 --> 00:33:55,646
Oskar Vallian is the mind
behind this theory, right?

632
00:33:55,670 --> 00:33:56,670
Well, guess what?

633
00:33:57,700 --> 00:33:59,446
He thinks Mount Fuji is gonna erupt

634
00:33:59,470 --> 00:34:01,113
within the next three weeks.

635
00:34:22,870 --> 00:34:27,009
- I want you and Konomi
to go back to Tokyo.

636
00:34:27,033 --> 00:34:29,523
- Konomi, there's a car
waiting for you outside.

637
00:34:30,580 --> 00:34:32,526
- Yes, but I'm not finished with my work.

638
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:34,013
- Just go.
- Yes, ma'am.

639
00:34:37,070 --> 00:34:38,386
- I said both of you.

640
00:34:38,410 --> 00:34:39,220
- Oskar.

641
00:34:39,244 --> 00:34:40,806
- You're a young woman

642
00:34:40,830 --> 00:34:43,196
and you have your entire
life ahead of you.

643
00:34:43,220 --> 00:34:45,576
- You've been my entire life for 12 years.

644
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:47,576
I'm not going to leave you now.

645
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:48,547
- Melanie.

646
00:34:48,571 --> 00:34:50,216
- Don't say anything,

647
00:34:50,240 --> 00:34:51,240
I'm staying.

648
00:35:12,490 --> 00:35:14,726
- And to that end, he's gone off to Honshu

649
00:35:14,750 --> 00:35:16,876
to gather data directly.

650
00:35:16,900 --> 00:35:20,283
In the meantime, I'll be going to Ecuador.

651
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:24,273
If our theory is correct

652
00:35:24,297 --> 00:35:26,166
and these recent volcanic events

653
00:35:26,190 --> 00:35:29,696
are like dominoes in a long chain,

654
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:32,132
each linked to a tectonic plate

655
00:35:32,156 --> 00:35:35,216
through a series of
interconnecting fault lines.

656
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:37,226
Our job would then be to ascertain,

657
00:35:37,250 --> 00:35:39,446
not only why all of this is happening,

658
00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:41,318
but which faults are being affected

659
00:35:41,342 --> 00:35:44,453
and which volcanoes are
likely to go off next.

660
00:35:46,850 --> 00:35:48,100
I'm not gonna lie to you,

661
00:35:49,140 --> 00:35:51,176
this is gonna be dangerous.

662
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:53,825
So if any of you have any reservations,

663
00:35:53,849 --> 00:35:56,186
especially after what happened in Iceland,

664
00:35:56,210 --> 00:35:58,513
believe me, I'll understand.

665
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:01,016
- It's not even an issue.

666
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:02,806
Count me in.

667
00:36:02,830 --> 00:36:04,146
- Me too.

668
00:36:04,170 --> 00:36:06,206
- Well, seeing that it's
the only chance we've got

669
00:36:06,230 --> 00:36:07,057
of proving any of this,

